      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Handy little clash here and GIN TWIST (1) is the one with the runs on the board. She placed in her first two starts before coming here in the Listed Festival Stakes and blowing them away over 1000m with good speed. The query is 1200m for the first time but she still ran the fastest last 200m of the meeting and if she handles the trip she'll go close. JADZIA (4) finally got to the racetrack after a few false starts, finding the line nicely behind another Hayes 2yo in Medicinal who won in good time. She looks set to relish 1200m now and can improve quickly. STAR JE TAIME (9) is a filly by Snitzel on debut for the O'Brien yard who has jumped out well and can measure up. SATONO GLOW (5) made good ground to win on debut at Warwick Farm. Respecting the yard to bring her down here. ",
